<DOC><DOCNO> AP881219-0271 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-19-88 1427EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-EEC-Airbus     12-19 0153</FIRST><SECOND>BC-EEC-Airbus,0160</SECOND><HEAD>EEC Bank to Make $133.5 Million Loan for Airbus</HEAD><DATELINE>LUXEMBOURG (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The European Investment Bank said Monday itwould lend 800 million French francs, or around $133.5 million, tothe French aircraft maker Aerospatiale for assembling AirbusA330-340 jetliners.   The bank, which is the long-term investment agency of theEuropean Economic Community, said the loan was for 20 years. Theinterest rate wasn't disclosed.   Aerospatiale, based in Toulouse, France, is the French member ofAirbus Industrie, a European aircraft consortium. The other membersare companies from West Germany, Britain and Spain.   The A330-340, the largest aircraft in the Airbus range, is along- and medium-range plane.   The bank said the loan is earmarked for new buildings andinstallations that will be used to improve assembly and researchfacilities at the site in Toulouse. Aircraft components supplied byfactories in the other Airbus member countries are assembled at thesite.</TEXT></DOC>